        Chassis weight includes oil, water, AdBlue, 0 litres fuel and without driver (315/80R22.5 wheels everywhere) => no option (sleeper cab, small fuel tank, etc)

        4x2
        5600kg front / 1930kg rear
        in game with fuel and driver and 385/65r22.5 steering wheels = 5920kg front axle and 2350kg rear = 8270kg

        6x4
        5400kg front / 3750kg rear
        in game with fuel and driver and 385/65r22.5 steering wheels = 5800kg front axle and 4050kg rear = 9850kg

        8x4 TAG or pusher
        5610kg front / 4655kg rear
        in game with fuel and driver and 385/65r22.5 steering wheels = 6050kg front axle and 5000kg rear = 11050kg


        wheels are set to 500kg each in base game (maybe to better handle the huge torque of the engine ?)
        should be something like 600kg for the 6

        component1 = main
        component2 = front axle

        hydraulic front wheel assist (up to 20kph) = "x-track" by Terberg
        front hubs should be colored
        44KW max per wheel
        => not present in game

        6x4 and 8x4 = the "towbar" (5th wheel) should be mounted closer toward the front of the truck. In the game, they are not "ideally" centered for the load (most of the load on the last axle)
        8x4 TAG = doesn't seem to be "realistic". rather something we would see on a rigid truck, not a semi

    -->

